__Software Defined Network__

from Georgia Tech
=================

1. Learn about the motivation(and origins ) of Software Defined Networking.
2. Understand current trends in SDN
3. Learn the types of networking problems SDN is good at solving.
4. Develop hands-on experience appling SDN to different domains.


#### What you will know by the end

* Apply SDN concepts to solve real network management problems
	1. Load balance in data-center and backbone networks.
	2. Security in enterprise networks.

* Set up your won SDN(in a virtual machine)

USE SDN to solve problems in data centers, interdomain routing, etc.


Course Prerequisite -- Python, basic socket programming in C, computer networking, Experience with the linux operating system, Virtual Box.

First activity : Pre-Assessment Quiz.


